BladeCommFault.Message: The server hardware in bay %1 cannot be discovered due to a communication failure.
BladeCommFault.Resolution: Remove the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert it. If the failure persists, replace the server hardware.

BladeCommFaultCleared.Message: The communication failure on the server hardware in bay %1 has cleared.

BladeConfigurationFault.Message: The server hardware in bay %1 will not be allowed to power on due to mezzanine card(s) %2 not matching the type of interconnect(s) %3.
BladeConfigurationFault.Resolution: Remove the server hardware in bay %1 and remove mezzanine card(s) %2 or move the card to a slot that matches the interconnect type. Then re-insert the server hardware. Alternatively, consider moving interconnect(s) %3 to a bay matching the mezzanine card type if multiple servers have this issue.

BladeConfigurationFaultCleared.Message: The mezzanine/interconnect mismatch was resolved for the server hardware in bay %1.

BladeEfusePGoodFault.Message: The device in bay %1 has failed.

BladeEfusePGoodFaultCleared.Message: The failure on the device in bay %1 has cleared.

BladeFault.Message: The device in bay %1 cannot be discovered.
BladeFault.Resolution: Remove the device in bay %1 and re-insert it. If the issue persists, replace the device.

BladeFaultCleared.Message: The issue preventing discovery of device in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeFruContentFault.Message: The device in bay %1 is missing hardware information and cannot be discovered.

BladeFruFault.Message: The device in bay %1 cannot be discovered.

BladeFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Message: The device in bay %1 is not compatible with the frame link module firmware version.
BladeFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Resolution: Update the frame link module firmware to a version that supports this device.

BladeFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Message: The device in bay %1 is not compatible with its (%2) enclosure.
BladeFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Resolution: Verify manufacturer of the device in bay %1 is compatible with its (%2) enclosure manufacturer.

BladeIloFailedCleared.Message: The issue causing an iLO boot failure for the server hardware in bay %1 has cleared.

BladeIloFailedCritical.Message: The iLO for the server hardware in bay %1 has failed to boot.
BladeIloFailedCritical.Resolution: Remove the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert it. If the issue persists, replace the server hardware.

BladeIloFruFault.Message: The server hardware in bay %1 cannot be discovered.
BladeIloFruFault.Resolution: Remove the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert.  Check the iLO Integrated Management Log for more information.  If the issue persists, replace the server hardware.

BladeIloFruFaultCleared.Message: The server hardware in bay %1 was successfully discovered after a retry.

BladeIloOperationalStatusCleared.Message: The iLO communication timeout for the server hardware in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeIloOperationalStatusCritical.Message: The iLO for the server hardware in bay %1 cannot be discovered.
BladeIloOperationalStatusCritical.Resolution: Remove the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert.  Alternatively, reset the frame link module.  If the issue persists, replace the server hardware.

BladeIloOperationalStatusWarning.Message: The iLO for the server hardware in bay %1 had a communication timeout.
BladeIloOperationalStatusWarning.Resolution: Reset the iLO for the server hardware in bay %1 via OneView or the hardware's iLO management interface.  Alternatively, remove the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert it.

BladeInsertFault.Message: The device in bay %1 cannot be discovered due to a presence failure.
BladeInsertFault.Resolution: Remove the device in bay %1 and re-insert.  If the failure persists, replace the device in bay %1.

BladeInsertFaultCleared.Message: The presence failure on the device in bay %1 has cleared.

BladeInserted.Message: A device has been inserted in bay %1.

BladeInsufficientCooling.Message: The device in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to insufficient cooling in the enclosure. All fan bays are required to have operational fans installed.

BladeInsufficientCoolingCleared.Message: The cooling issue for the device in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeInsufficientPower.Message: The device in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to insufficient power in the enclosure.
BladeInsufficientPower.Resolution: Insert additional power supplies, if possible. Consider changing the input power mode for the logical enclosure to "Redundant power supply."

BladeInsufficientPowerCleared.Message: The insufficient power issue for the device in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeManagerFault.Message: The device in bay %1 experienced a communication timeout with the frame link module.
BladeManagerFault.Resolution: Remove the device in bay %1 and re-insert it.

BladeManagerFaultCleared.Message: The device in bay %1 resumed communication with the frame link module.

BladeManagerICMReadyFault.Message: The management processor for the device in bay %1 is not ready.
BladeManagerICMReadyFault.Resolution: Remove the device in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the device.

BladeManagerICMReadyFaultCleared.Message: The management processor for the device in bay %1 is ready.

BladeManagerIloInternalCritical.Message: The iLO for the server hardware in bay %1 is reporting that the server hardware has a critical internal health status.
BladeManagerIloInternalCritical.Resolution: Check the iLO System Information - Health Summary and Integrated Management Log for more information. Remove the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the server hardware.

BladeManagerIloInternalCriticalCleared.Message: The issue causing a critical internal health status for the server hardware in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeManagerIloInternalWarning.Message: The iLO for the server hardware in bay %1 is reporting that the server hardware has a warning internal health status.
BladeManagerIloInternalWarning.Resolution: Check the iLO System Information - Health Summary and Integrated Management Log for more information. Remove the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the server hardware.

BladeManagerIloInternalWarningCleared.Message: The issue causing a warning internal health status for the server hardware in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeManagerInternalCritical.Message: The management processor on the device in bay %1 is reporting a critical internal health status.
BladeManagerInternalCritical.Resolution: View the activity log for the device in bay %1 or the SAS Connection Module(s); follow the recommendations to resolve any issues.  If the activity log for the device doesn't have recommendations, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

BladeManagerInternalCriticalCleared.Message: The issue causing a critical internal health status for the management processor on the device in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeManagerInternalWarning.Message: The management processor on the device in bay %1 is reporting a warning internal health status.
BladeManagerInternalWarning.Resolution: View the activity log for the device in bay %1 or the SAS Connection Module(s); follow the recommendations to resolve any issues.  If the activity log for the device doesn't have recommendations, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

BladeManagerInternalWarningCleared.Message: The issue causing a warning internal health status for the management processor on the device in bay %1 was resolved.

BladeMateDetectFault.Message: The device in bay %1 is not seated properly in its bay.
BladeMateDetectFault.Resolution: Remove the device, inspect for damage, and replace if necessary.  Re-insert if not damaged.

BladeMateDetectFaultCleared.Message: The device in bay %1 is now seated properly.

BladeMezzFruContentFault.Message: The mezzanine card(s) installed in the server hardware in bay %1 is/are missing hardware information and cannot be discovered.
BladeMezzFruContentFault.Resolution: Replace the mezzanine card(s) installed in the server hardware in bay %1.

BladeMezzFruFault.Message: The mezzanine card(s) installed on the server hardware in bay %1 cannot be discovered.
BladeMezzFruFault.Resolution: Check the iLO Integrated Management Log for more information.  Verify the iLO firmware is the latest Synergy Software Release version.  Remove the mezzanine card(s) in the server hardware in bay %1 and re-insert them.  If the issue persists, replace the failing mezzanine card(s).

BladeMezzFruFaultCleared.Message: The mezzanine card(s) installed on the server hardware in bay %1 was successfully discovered after a retry.

BladeMezzFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Message: Mezzanine card(s) %2 installed in the server hardware in bay %1 is/are not compatible with the frame link module firmware version.
BladeMezzFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Resolution: Update the frame link module firmware to a version that supports the mezzanine card(s).

BladeMezzFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Message: Mezzanine card(s) %2 installed in the server hardware in bay %1 is/are not compatible with its/their (%3) enclosure.
BladeMezzFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Resolution: Verify manufacturer of mezzanine card(s) %2 in the server hardware in bay %1 is compatible with the (%3) enclosure manufacturer.

BladePowerDeniedDueToFru.Message: The device in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to a failure to obtain identifying hardware information.
BladePowerDeniedDueToFru.Resolution: View the activity log for the device in bay %1; follow the recommendations to resolve any issues.

BladePowerDeniedDueToMating.Message: The device in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to a connector mating issue.
BladePowerDeniedDueToMating.Resolution: Remove the device, inspect for damage, and replace if necessary.  Re-insert if not damaged.

BladePowerDeniedDueToMatingCleared.Message: The connector mating issue for the device in bay %1 was resolved.

BladePowerDeniedDueToMidplane.Message: The device in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to an issue discovering the enclosure midplane.
BladePowerDeniedDueToMidplane.Resolution: View the activity log for the enclosure; follow the recommendations to resolve any issues.

BladeRedundantCommFault.Message: The device in bay %1 encountered a failure with one of its two redundant internal management links. The device is still manageable but communication redundancy has been lost.
BladeRedundantCommFault.Resolution: Remove the device in bay %1 and inspect its connector for damage. Re-insert the device if no damage is seen.  If the failure persists, replace the device.

BladeRedundantCommFaultCleared.Message: The failure of the redundant internal management link on the device in bay %1 has cleared.

BladeRemoved.Message: The device in bay %1 has been removed.

BladeSystemPGoodFault.Message: The device in bay %1 has failed.

BladeSystemPGoodFaultCleared.Message: The issue with the device in bay %1 has been resolved.

BladeThermalCritical.Message: The device in bay %1 was powered off because the temperature exceeded the critical threshold.
BladeThermalCritical.Resolution: Check the status of the fans. Remove the device in bay %1 and ensure there is no blockage to the cooling inlets, then re-insert the device.

BladeThermalOk.Message: The temperature for the server hardware in bay %1 is within operational limits.

BladeThermalWarning.Message: The device in bay %1 has reached the warning temperature threshold.
BladeThermalWarning.Resolution: Check the status of the fans. Remove the device in bay %1 and ensure there is no blockage to the cooling inlets, then re-insert the device.

BladeUnsupportedDeviceFault.Message: The device in bay %1 is not compatible with the frame link module firmware version currently installed.
BladeUnsupportedDeviceFault.Resolution: Update the frame link module firmware to a version with support for the device in bay %1.

CIManagerCommFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 cannot be discovered due to a communication failure.
CIManagerCommFault.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the failure persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerCommFaultCleared.Message: The communication failure on the appliance in bay %1 has cleared.

CIManagerEfusePGoodFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 has failed.

CIManagerEfusePGoodFaultCleared.Message: The failure on the appliance in bay %1 has cleared.

CIManagerFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 cannot be discovered.
CIManagerFault.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerFaultCleared.Message: The issue preventing discovery of the appliance in bay %1 was resolved.

CIManagerFruContentFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 is missing hardware information and cannot be discovered.

CIManagerFruFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 cannot be discovered.
CIManagerFruFault.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 is not compatible with the frame link module firmware version.
CIManagerFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Resolution: Update the frame link module firmware to a version that supports the appliance in bay %1.

CIManagerFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 is not compatible with its (%2) enclosure.
CIManagerFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Resolution: Verify manufacturer of the appliance in bay %1 is compatible with its (%2) enclosure manufacturer.

CIManagerIloFault.Message: The iLO for the appliance in bay %1 has a communication timeout.
CIManagerIloFault.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerIloFaultCleared.Message: The iLO communication timeout for the appliance in bay %1 has cleared.

CIManagerIloInternalCritical.Message: The appliance in bay %1 has a critical internal health status.
CIManagerIloInternalCritical.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerIloInternalCriticalCleared.Message: The critical internal health status for the appliance in bay %1 has cleared.

CIManagerIloInternalWarning.Message: The appliance in bay %1 has a warning internal health status.
CIManagerIloInternalWarning.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerIloInternalWarningCleared.Message: The warning internal health status for the appliance in bay %1 has cleared.

CIManagerInsertFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 cannot be discovered due to a presence failure.
CIManagerInsertFault.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the failure persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerInsertFaultCleared.Message: The presence failure on the appliance in bay %1 has cleared.

CIManagerInserted.Message: The appliance in bay %1 has been inserted.

CIManagerRedundantCommFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 encountered a failure with one of its two redundant internal management links. The appliance is still manageable but communication redundancy has been lost.
CIManagerRedundantCommFault.Resolution: Remove the appliance in bay %1 and inspect its connector for damage. Re-insert the appliance if no damage is seen.  If the failure persists, replace the appliance.

CIManagerRedundantCommFaultCleared.Message: The failure of the redundant internal management link on the appliance in bay %1 has cleared.

CIManagerRemoved.Message: The appliance in bay %1 has been removed.

CIManagerUnsupportedDeviceFault.Message: The appliance in bay %1 is not compatible with the frame link module firmware version currently installed.
CIManagerUnsupportedDeviceFault.Resolution: Update the frame link module firmware to a version with support for the appliance in bay %1.

ChassisAmbientThermal.Message: The enclosure ambient temperature (%1 °C) has exceeded the operating temperature limit associated with the configured ambient temperature mode (%2 °C).
ChassisAmbientThermal.Resolution: Verify the facility air conditioning system is providing adequate cooling.  Check the front of the enclosure and remove any airflow blockage.  Consider changing the ambient temperature mode.  If the issue persists, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

ChassisAmbientThermalCleared.Message: The enclosure ambient temperature is within the operating temperature limits for the configured ambient temperature mode.

ChassisEventServiceSubscriptionOverrunFa.Message: The frame link module cannot communicate with the OneView appliance.
The frame link module can now communicate with the OneView appliance.

ChassisRedundantCommFault.Message: The enclosure encountered a failure with one of its two redundant internal management links. Devices in the enclosure are still manageable but communication redundancy has been lost.
ChassisRedundantCommFault.Resolution: If the failure persists, replace the enclosure.  Note that this issue can be caused by damage to connectors on one or more enclosure components and/or the corresponding mating connector(s) on the enclosure midplane. Carefully inspect connectors prior to inserting or swapping enclosure components to avoid potentially propagating damage to additional components.

ChassisRedundantCommFaultCleared.Message: The failure of the redundant internal management link on the enclosure has cleared.

ChassisRemoteLoggingFault.Message: The frame link module cannot communicate with the remote logging server.
ChassisRemoteLoggingFault.Resolution: Verify the remote logging server configuration and the frame link module network. If TLS-based logging is configured, verify the remote logging server certificates are correct.

ChassisRemoteLoggingFaultCleared.Message: The frame link module can now communicate with the remote logging server or remote logging was disabled.

DevicePowerThrottlingActive.Message: Devices in the enclosure are being power throttled to ensure that utilized power does not exceed available power.
DevicePowerThrottlingActive.Resolution: Resolve all power supply alerts.  Ensure all power supplies are inserted properly with input power applied.  Consider inserting additional power supplies, if possible.

DevicePowerThrottlingActiveCleared.Message: Devices in the enclosure are no longer being power throttled.

EmBooting.Message: A frame link module has restarted.  Any hardware related alerts on the enclosure have been cleared and will appear again if the issue(s) still exist.

EmClusterResourceCleared.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has successfully established redundant management.

EmClusterResourceFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 was unable to establish redundant management of the enclosure.
EmClusterResourceFault.Resolution: Reset the frame link module in bay %1 or remove and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the frame link module.

EmCommFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has a communication failure with its partner module.
EmCommFault.Resolution: Reset the frame link module in bay %1 or remove and re-insert it.  If the failure persists, replace the frame link module.

EmCommFaultCleared.Message: The communication failure on the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmDataReplicationFault.Message: The standby frame link module in bay %1 contains configuration data which is inconsistent with the active frame link module.  There is a potential for data loss if this issue is not resolved.
EmDataReplicationFault.Resolution: Reset the standby frame link module in bay %1 or remove and re-insert it.  The active frame link module should not be reset while the standby is in this state.  If the issue persists, replace the standby frame link module.

EmDataReplicationFaultCleared.Message: Configuration data on the standby frame link module in bay %1 is now consistent with the active frame link module.

EmDiskEncryptionFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 failed to create or access encrypted persistent storage.
EmDiskEncryptionFault.Resolution: Remove and re-insert the frame link module in bay %1. If the problem persists, contact your authorized support representative.

EmDiskEncryptionFaultCleared.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 was able to create and access encrypted persistent storage.

EmFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has failed a power-on test.
EmFault.Resolution: Reset the frame link module in bay %1 or remove and re-insert it.  If the failure persists, replace the frame link module.

EmFaultCleared.Message: The power-on test failure for the frame link module in bay %1 was resolved.

EmFruContentFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 is missing hardware information and cannot be discovered.
EmFruContentFault.Resolution: Replace the frame link module in bay %1.

EmFruFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 cannot be discovered.
EmFruFault.Resolution: Reset the frame link module in bay %1 or remove and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the frame link module.

EmFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 is not compatible with the frame link module firmware version.
EmFruManufacturedForInvalidFault.Resolution: Update the firmware in the frame link module in bay %1 to a version that is supported.

EmFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 is not compatible with its (%2) enclosure.
EmFruManufacturedForMismatchFault.Resolution: Verify manufacturer of the frame link module in bay %1 is compatible with its (%2) enclosure manufacturer.

EmFuseFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has failed.
EmFuseFault.Resolution: Remove the frame link module in bay %1 and contact your authorized support representative.

EmFwMatch.Message: The firmware mismatch on the frame link module in bay %1 was resolved.

EmFwMismatch.Message: The standby frame link module in bay %1 has a firmware mismatch with the active frame link module.
EmFwMismatch.Resolution: Reset the standby frame link module in bay %1, or remove and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the standby frame link module.

EmHighAssuranceBootCritical.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 failed to securely boot. The integrity of the booted firmware image was not properly validated.
EmHighAssuranceBootCritical.Resolution: Replace the frame link module in bay %1.

EmHwMismatch.Message: There are mismatched frame link modules in the enclosure.  All frame link modules within an enclosure must be of the same model type.
EmHwMismatch.Resolution: Ensure the enclosure contains only one type of frame link module.  Replace the mismatched frame link module.

EmImageManagerLinkDisconnected.Message: The MGMT port for the frame link module in bay %1 is unlinked. It must be linked to the Image Streamer deployment network because an Image Streamer appliance is present in the enclosure. {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmImageManagerLinkDisconnected.Resolution: Connect the MGMT port from the frame link module to the Image Streamer deployment network.  Ensure the cable is functioning properly and it is a compatible cable type.  Check the status of the connected network devices.

EmImageManagerLinkDisconnectedCleared_Mg.Message: The issue with the MGMT port on the frame link module in bay %1 was resolved.
A link for an Image Streamer appliance is no longer required on the MGMT port for the frame link module in bay %1.

EmInsertFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 cannot be discovered due to a presence failure.
EmInsertFault.Resolution: Reset the frame link module in bay %1 or remove and re-insert it.  If the failure persists, replace the frame link module.

EmInsertFaultCleared.Message: The presence failure on the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmInserted.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has been inserted.

EmInternalLinkDisconnected.Message: The internal link port on the frame link module in bay %1 has lost communication with its peer frame link module.
EmInternalLinkDisconnected.Resolution: Individually, remove both of the frame link modules in the enclosure and re-insert them.  If the issue persists, further hardware analysis is required.

EmInternalLinkDisconnectedCleared_Intern.Message: The internal link port on the frame link module in bay %1 has re-established communication with its peer frame link module.

EmInternalLinkDisconnectedCleared_PeerEm.Message: The internal link port on the frame link module in bay %1 has lost communication with its peer frame link module.
EmInternalLinkDisconnectedCleared_PeerEm.Resolution: If the enclosure does not have both frame link modules installed, insert the missing frame link module.  Otherwise, remove the standby frame link module and re-insert it.  If that does not resolve the issue, remove the active frame link module and re-insert it.

EmIsActive.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 is active.

EmLinkConnectedIncorrectly.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is connected to an unknown device. A frame link module may only be connected to another frame link module's LINK port. {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmLinkConnectedIncorrectly.Resolution: Connect the LINK port from the frame link module in bay %1 to another frame link module in an enclosure managed by this appliance.

EmLinkConnectedIncorrectlyCleared_LinkLo.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is no longer linked to an unknown device.

EmLinkConnectedIncorrectlyCleared_Owners.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is now connected properly to another frame link module's LINK port.

EmLinkDisconnected.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is not connected. {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmLinkDisconnected.Resolution: Connect the LINK port from the frame link module in bay %1 to another frame link module in an enclosure managed by this appliance. Ensure the cable is functioning properly and it is a compatible cable type.  Check the status of the connected frame link module.

EmLinkDisconnectedCleared_LinkDetected.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is connected to another frame link module.

EmLinkDisconnectedCleared_PeerEmRemoved.Message: The LINK port for the frame link module in bay %1 no longer requires connection because the peer frame link module is not present.

EmLinkNeighborInfoExpired.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 is no longer receiving information from the frame link module cabled to the LINK port.
EmLinkNeighborInfoExpired.Resolution: Reset the frame link module in bay %1 or remove and re-insert it.  Complete the same steps with the frame link module cabled to the LINK port.

EmLinkNeighborInfoExpiredCleared.Message: The neighbor link information issue on the LINK port of the frame link module in bay %1 has been resolved.

EmLinkNeighborOwnerMismatch.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is connected to frame link module %3 in enclosure %2 that is not managed by this appliance. As a result, it is not possible to communicate with the connected frame link module. {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmLinkNeighborOwnerMismatch.Resolution: If the enclosure cabled to the frame link module in bay %1 is not cabled properly, disconnect the LINK port from the frame link module and re-cable it to another frame link module in an enclosure managed by this appliance. Alternatively, if the intent is to manage the enclosure, then enclosure %2 must be factory reset before it can be managed by this appliance. A factory reset will remove all prior configuration from the enclosure.

EmLinkNeighborOwnerMismatchCleared_LinkL.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is no longer connected to an enclosure that is not managed by this appliance.

EmMau1GbTransceiverAppliancePort1.Message: An unsupported transceiver is present in appliance port 1 of the frame link module in bay %1.  Appliance ports require 10Gb transceivers.
EmMau1GbTransceiverAppliancePort1.Resolution: Replace the transceiver in appliance port 1 with a 10Gb transceiver.

EmMau1GbTransceiverAppliancePort1Cleared.Message: The unsupported transceiver was removed from appliance port 1 of the frame link module in bay %1.

EmMau1GbTransceiverAppliancePort2.Message: An unsupported transceiver is present in appliance port 2 of the frame link module in bay %1.  Appliance ports require 10Gb transceivers.
EmMau1GbTransceiverAppliancePort2.Resolution: Replace the transceiver in appliance port 2 with a 10Gb transceiver.

EmMau1GbTransceiverAppliancePort2Cleared.Message: The unsupported transceiver was removed from appliance port 2 of the frame link module in bay %1.

EmMau1GbTransceiverElinkPort.Message: An unsupported transceiver is present in the LINK port of the frame link module in bay %1.  LINK ports require 10Gb transceivers.
EmMau1GbTransceiverElinkPort.Resolution: Replace the transceiver in the LINK port with a 10Gb transceiver.

EmMau1GbTransceiverElinkPortCleared.Message: The unsupported transceiver was removed from the LINK port for the frame link module in bay %1.

EmMauIncompatibleHardwareAppliancePort1.Message: The appliance in bay 1 or the frame midplane does not support transmitting and receiving data on appliance port 1 of the frame link module in bay %1.
EmMauIncompatibleHardwareAppliancePort1.Resolution: Update the frame hardware configuration with compatible components or remove any connected cable/transceiver from appliance port 1.

EmMauIncompatibleHardwareCleared_Applian.Message: The frame hardware configuration supports transmitting and receiving data on appliance port 1 of the frame link module in bay %1 or there is no longer anything inserted.

EmMauIncompatibleHardwareAppliancePort2.Message: The appliance in bay 2 or the frame midplane does not support transmitting and receiving data on appliance port 2 of the frame link module in bay %1.
EmMauIncompatibleHardwareAppliancePort2.Resolution: Update the frame hardware configuration with compatible components or remove any connected cable/transceiver from appliance port 2.

EmMauIncompatibleHardwareCleared_Applian.Message: The frame hardware configuration supports transmitting and receiving data on appliance port 2 of the frame link module in bay %1 or there is no longer anything inserted.

EmMauTransceiverFailureAppliancePort1.Message: Appliance port 1 of the frame link module in bay %1 has a transmit or receive fault.
EmMauTransceiverFailureAppliancePort1.Resolution: Verify that a supported cable/transceiver is attached to the port.   If the problem persists, replace the cable/transceiver for appliance port 1.

EmMauTransceiverFailureAppliancePort1Cle.Message: The fault on appliance port 1 of the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.
The fault on appliance port 1 of frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmMauTransceiverFailureAppliancePort2.Message: Appliance port 2 of the frame link module in bay %1 has a transmit or receive fault.
EmMauTransceiverFailureAppliancePort2.Resolution: Verify that a supported cable/transceiver is attached to the port.   If the problem persists, replace the cable/transceiver for appliance port 2.

EmMauTransceiverFailureAppliancePort2Cle.Message: The fault on appliance port 2 of the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.
The fault on appliance port 2 of frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmMauTransceiverFailureElinkPort.Message: The LINK port of the frame link module in bay %1 has a transmit or receive fault.
EmMauTransceiverFailureElinkPort.Resolution: Verify that a supported cable/transceiver is attached to the port.   If the problem persists, replace the cable/transceiver for the LINK port.

EmMauTransceiverFailureElinkPortCleared.Message: The fault on the LINK port of the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmMauTransceiverFailureElinkPortCleared_.Message: The fault on the LINK port of frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmMauTransceiverFailureMgmtPort.Message: The MGMT port of the frame link module in bay %1 has a transmit or receive fault.
EmMauTransceiverFailureMgmtPort.Resolution: Verify that a supported cable/transceiver is attached to the port.   If the problem persists, replace the cable/transceiver for the MGMT port.

EmMauTransceiverFailureMgmtPortCleared.Message: The fault on the MGMT port of the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmMauTransceiverFailureMgmtPortCleared_D.Message: The fault on the MGMT port of the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmMgmtPortConnectedIncorrectly.Message: The MGMT port on the frame link module in bay %1 is connected to another frame link module and that is not a valid connection. The MGMT port may only be connected to the management network.  {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmMgmtPortConnectedIncorrectly.Resolution: Connect the MGMT port from the frame link module to the management network.

EmMgmtPortConnectedIncorrectlyCleared_Mg.Message: The MGMT port for the frame link module in bay %1 is now propertly connected to a management network.
The MGMT port for the frame link module in bay %1 is no longer connected to another frame link module.

EmMgmtPortConnectedIncorrectlyImageManag.Message: The MGMT port on the frame link module in bay %1 is connected to another frame link module and that is not a valid connection. The MGMT port may only be connected to the Image Streamer deployment network.  {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmMgmtPortConnectedIncorrectlyImageManag.Resolution: Re-cable the MGMT port on the frame link module to the Image Streamer deployment network.

EmMissing.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 is missing.
EmMissing.Resolution: Add a second frame link module and connect its LINK port to another frame link module in an enclosure managed by this appliance.

EmMissingCleared.Message: The missing frame link module is now present.

EmNTPTimeSync.Message: The frame link module cannot synchronize time with the OneView appliance.
EmNTPTimeSync.Resolution: Refresh the enclosure.  Update the Time and Locale settings to resynchronize the time service.

EmNTPTimeSyncCleared.Message: The frame link module has successfully synchronized time with the OneView appliance.

EmOneViewLinkDisconnected.Message: The MGMT port for the frame link module in bay %1 is unlinked.  It should be linked to the management network because a OneView appliance is present in appliance bay %1. {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmOneViewLinkDisconnected.Resolution: Connect the MGMT port from the frame link module to the management network to ensure the most resilient connection to the management network.  Ensure the cable is functioning properly and it is a compatible cable type.  Check the status of the connected network devices.

EmOneViewLinkDisconnectedCleared_MgmtPor.Message: The issue with the MGMT port on the frame link module in bay %1 was resolved.
A link for a OneView appliance is no longer required on the MGMT port for the frame link module in bay %1.

EmOneViewLinkDisconnectedCleared_OneView.Message: The MGMT port on the frame link module in bay %1 no longer requires a link since a OneView appliance is no longer present.

EmOneViewLinkValidationPingAddressMismat.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 does not have a compatible address type and failed to ping %2.
EmOneViewLinkValidationPingAddressMismat.Resolution: Specify the ping validation address.  Alternatively, configure the frame link module in bay %1 with an IP address of the appropriate type to validate if the MGMT port is on the right network.

EmOneViewLinkValidationPingAddressMismat.Message: The failure on the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmOneViewLinkValidationPingFailed.Message: The MGMT port on the frame link module in bay %1 cannot ping the requested network address %2.
EmOneViewLinkValidationPingFailed.Resolution: Verify MGMT port is connected to the correct network or change the MGMT port validation address.

EmOneViewLinkValidationPingFailedCleared.Message: The MGMT port ping failure on the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.
The validation of the MGMT port connectivity has been disabled on the frame link module in bay %1.

EmOneViewLinkValidationPingFailed_Cleare.Message: The MGMT port ping failure on the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmPeerEmNeeded.Message: The LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 is linked but a redundant frame link module is missing. A redundant frame link module is expected if the LINK port is linked. {"name":"Learn More","uri":"/doc#/cic/enclosures/linkmodule/learn"}
EmPeerEmNeeded.Resolution: Insert the redundant frame link module or disconnect the LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1.

EmPeerEmNeededCleared_ElinkRemoved.Message: A redundant frame link module is no longer required because the LINK port on the frame link module in bay %1 has been unlinked.

EmPeerEmNeededCleared_PeerEmInserted.Message: The missing redundant frame link module has been inserted.

EmRedundantCommFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 encountered a failure with one of its two redundant internal management links. The frame link module is still manageable but communication redundancy has been lost.
EmRedundantCommFault.Resolution: Remove the frame link module in bay %1 and inspect its connector for damage. Re-insert the frame link module if no damage is seen. If the failure persists, replace the frame link module.

EmRedundantCommFaultCleared.Message: The failure of the redundant internal management link on the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmRemoved.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has been removed.

EmSwitchCommunicationCritical.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has an internal failure.
EmSwitchCommunicationCritical.Resolution: Remove the frame link module in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the failure persists, replace the frame link module.

EmSwitchCommunicationOk.Message: The internal failure with the frame link module in bay %1 has cleared.

EmSwitchHardwareCritical.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has a hardware failure.
EmSwitchHardwareCritical.Resolution: Replace the frame link module in bay %1.

EmSwitchHardwareOk.Message: The previously detected hardware failure has cleared.

EmThermalCritical.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has exceeded the critical temperature threshold.
EmThermalCritical.Resolution: Resolve any fan or cooling alerts for the enclosure. Remove the frame link module and ensure there is no blockage to the cooling inlets; then re-insert it.

EmThermalOk.Message: The temperature for the frame link module in bay %1 is within operational limits.

EmThermalSensorReadOk.Message: Temperature was read for the frame link module in bay %1.

EmThermalSensorReadWarning.Message: Unable to read temperature sensor for the frame link module in bay %1.
EmThermalSensorReadWarning.Resolution: Reset the frame link module in bay %1 or remove the frame link module and re-insert it.

EmThermalWarning.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 has exceeded the warning temperature threshold.
EmThermalWarning.Resolution: Resolve any fan or cooling alerts for the enclosure. Remove the frame link module and ensure there is no blockage to the cooling inlets; then re-insert it.

EmTpmFwUpdateFault.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 failed to update its TPM firmware.
EmTpmFwUpdateFault.Resolution: Remove and re-insert the frame link module in bay %1. If the problem persists, contact your authorized support representative.

EmTpmFwUpdateFaultCleared.Message: The frame link module in bay %1 successfully updated its TPM firmware.

EmTpmStateMismatchFault.Message: The TPM on one frame link module is enabled while the TPM on the other frame link module is disabled.
EmTpmStateMismatchFault.Resolution: Ensure that the TPMs on both FLMs are either enabled or disabled.  Encryption of persistent storage on the frame link modules is only performed when both TPMs are enabled.

EmTpmStateMismatchFaultCleared.Message: The TPMs on the frame link modules are no longer in an incompatible state because the standby frame link module was removed.

FanCommFault.Message: The fan in bay %1 has a communication failure.

FanCommFaultCleared.Message: The communication failure on the fan in bay %1 has cleared.

FanInserted.Message: The fan in bay %1 has been inserted.

FanRedundantCommFaultCleared.Message: The failure of the redundant internal management link on the fan in bay %1 has cleared.

InsufficientFansCritical.Message: The enclosure does not have the required fans to be sufficiently cooled. All fan bays are required to have operational fans installed.

InterconnectEfusePGoodFault.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 has failed.

InterconnectInsufficientCoolingCleared.Message: The cooling issue for the interconnect in bay %1 was resolved.

InterconnectInsufficientPower.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to insufficient power in the enclosure.
InterconnectInsufficientPower.Resolution: Insert additional power supplies, if possible. Consider changing the input power mode for the logical enclosure to "Redundant power supply".

InterconnectInsufficientPowerCleared.Message: The insufficient power issue for the interconnect in bay %1 was resolved.

InterconnectManagerICMReadyFault.Message: The management processor on the interconnect in bay %1 did not start within the allotted time.
InterconnectManagerICMReadyFault.Resolution: This issue will clear when the management processor starts.  If it does not, remove the interconnect in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, then replace the interconnect.

InterconnectManagerICMReadyFaultCleared.Message: The management processor on the interconnect in bay %1 is ready.

InterconnectManagerInternalCritical.Message: The management processor on the interconnect in bay %1 is reporting a critical internal health status.
InterconnectManagerInternalCritical.Resolution: View the activity log for the interconnect in bay %1; follow the recommendations to resolve any issues.  If the activity log for the device doesn't have recommendations, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

InterconnectManagerInternalCriticalClear.Message: The issue causing a critical internal health status for the management processor on the interconnect in bay %1 was resolved.

InterconnectManagerInternalWarning.Message: The management processor on the interconnect in bay %1 is reporting a warning internal health status.
InterconnectManagerInternalWarning.Resolution: View the activity log for the interconnect in bay %1; follow the recommendations to resolve any issues.  If the activity log for the device doesn't have recommendations, contact your authorized support representative and provide them with a support dump.

InterconnectManagerInternalWarningCleare.Message: The issue causing a warning internal health status for the management processor on the interconnect in bay %1 was resolved.

InterconnectMateDetectFault.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 is not seated properly in its bay.
InterconnectMateDetectFault.Resolution: Remove the interconnect in bay %1, inspect for damage, and replace if necessary.  Re-insert if not damaged.

InterconnectMateDetectFaultCleared.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 is now seated properly.

InterconnectPowerDeniedDueToFru.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to a failure to obtain identifying hardware information.
InterconnectPowerDeniedDueToFru.Resolution: View the activity log for the interconnect in bay %1; follow the recommendations to resolve any failures.

InterconnectPowerDeniedDueToMatingCleare.Message: The connector mating issue for the interconnect in bay %1 was resolved.

InterconnectPowerDeniedDueToMidplane.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 was not allowed to power on due to an issue discovering the enclosure midplane.
InterconnectPowerDeniedDueToMidplane.Resolution: View the activity log for the enclosure; follow the recommendations to resolve any issues.

InterconnectRedundantCommFault.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 encountered a failure with one of its two redundant internal management links. The interconnect is still manageable but communication redundancy has been lost.
InterconnectRedundantCommFault.Resolution: Remove the interconnect in bay %1 and inspect its connector for damage. Re-insert interconnect if no damage is seen. If the failure persists, replace the interconnect.

InterconnectRedundantCommFaultCleared.Message: The failure of the redundant internal management link on the interconnect in bay %1 has cleared.

InterconnectRemoved.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 has been removed.

InterconnectSystemPGoodFault.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 has failed.

InterconnectSystemPGoodFaultCleared.Message: The failure with the interconnect in bay %1 has been resolved.

InterconnectThermalCritical.Message: The interconnect in bay %1 was powered off because the temperature exceeded the critical threshold.
InterconnectThermalCritical.Resolution: Check the status of the fans. Remove the interconnect and ensure there is no blockage to the cooling inlets, then re-insert it.

InterconnectThermalOk.Message: The temperature for the interconnect in bay %1 is within operational limits.

MidplaneFruContentFault.Message: The enclosure midplane is missing hardware information and cannot be discovered.

OneViewServiceEventsCommFault.Message: The frame link module cannot communicate remote support events to the OneView appliance.
OneViewServiceEventsCommFault.Resolution: Verify that the active OneView appliance is operational and has network connectivity to this enclosure.  Refresh the enclosure.

OneViewServiceEventsCommFaultCleared.Message: The frame link module can now send remote support events to the OneView appliance.

PowerSubsystemMismatchCleared.Message: The power supply mismatch issue was resolved.

PowerSubsystemOverLimit.Message: The enclosure is consuming more power than the specified limit allows.

PowerSupplyPsOkFault.Message: The output of the power supply in bay %1 is outside of tolerance.
PowerSupplyPsOkFault.Resolution: Remove the power supply in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the power supply.

PowerSupplyRedundantCommFault.Message: The power supply in bay %1 encountered a failure with one of its two redundant internal management links. The power supply is still manageable but communication redundancy has been lost.
PowerSupplyRedundantCommFault.Resolution: Remove the power supply in bay %1 and inspect its connector for damage. Re-insert the power supply if no damage is seen. If the failure persists, replace the power supply.

PowerSupplyRedundantCommFaultCleared.Message: The failure of the redundant internal management link on the power supply in bay %1 has cleared.

PowerSupplyReinsertFault.Message: The power supply in bay %1 has shut down.
PowerSupplyReinsertFault.Resolution: Remove the power supply in bay %1 and re-insert it.  If the issue persists, replace the power supply. (Error code: %2)

PowerSupplyRemoved.Message: The power supply in bay %1 has been removed.

PowerSupplyReplaceFault.Message: The power supply in bay %1 has shut down due to a critical failure.
PowerSupplyReplaceFault.Resolution: Replace the power supply in bay %1. (Error code: %2)

PowerSupplyUnsupportedDeviceFault.Message: The power supply in bay %1 is not compatible with the frame link module firmware version currently installed.
PowerSupplyUnsupportedDeviceFault.Resolution: Update the frame link module firmware to a version with support for the power supply in bay %1.

RingNoActiveMgmtPort.Message: The frame link topology does not have an active MGMT uplink port.  As a result, there is no management network connectivity to devices outside the topology.
RingNoActiveMgmtPort.Resolution: Connect a MGMT port from one of the frame link modules within the topology to the management network.

RingNoActiveMgmtPortCleared.Message: Connectivity to devices outside the topology has been restored.

RingNoActiveMgmtPortCleared_OwnerChanged.Message: The frame link module in this enclosure is no longer responsible for reporting frame link topology failures due to a change in topology ownership.

RingNoActiveMgmtPort_RingDegraded.Message: The frame link topology is not complete and does not have an active MGMT uplink port.  As a result, there is no management network connectivity to devices outside the topology.
RingNoActiveMgmtPort_RingDegraded.Resolution: Ensure all LINK ports are properly connected.  Connect a MGMT port from one of the frame link modules within the topology to the management network.

RingNoStandbyMgmtPort.Message: The frame link topology does not have redundant MGMT uplink port connections to the external management network.
RingNoStandbyMgmtPort.Resolution: Verify that at least two MGMT ports for frame link modules within the frame link topology are correctly connected to the external management network to achieve redundancy.

RingNoStandbyMgmtPortCleared.Message: The frame link topology has redundant MGMT uplink port connections to the external management network.

RingNoStandbyMgmtPortCleared_OwnerChange.Message: The frame link module in this frame is no longer managing the frame link topology.  The fault may be reasserted by the frame link module that has assumed the management of the frame link topology if there is still no redundant MGMT uplink port connection to the external management network.

RisTestEvent.Message: This event verifies proper operation of the frame link module event infrastructure.

SubscriptionCreated.Message: RIS event subscription is successfully created

Name: OneView Registry for Synergy Frame Link Module Messages
